    "summary": "I believe that good land administration practices hold great promise for increasing a country's social stability and strengthening economic growth. \n\nLocal land policies international guidelines require effective instruments for their implementation. Good land administration practices provide these tools. \n\nLand is becoming a increasingly scarce commodity. It is required for residential purposes, for food production, as an industrial resource or for transport and communication. This makes effective land administration practices even more urgent and crucial.      \n\nTo unleash this great potential of land administration, a wide expertise in a diversity of fields is required.  Amongst them are geodesy, information technology, law and sociology. Skills are essential too, especially social-, analytical-, advisory-, management- and communications skills. \n\nThroughout my personal career I have been able to build and mature this wide range of expertises and skills, and I find it very satisfying to be able to work in an environment that allows me to share this expertise, to support my collegues building and optimising their land administrations.",
